25/05/2007
PRISTINA, Kosovo, Serbia -- President Fatmir Sejdiu appointed members to a commission Thursday (May 24th) that will draft Kosovo's Constitution. 
Once the commission, headed by Hajredin Kuqi, of the Democratic Party of Kosovo, completes its work, the document would be forwarded to Parliament for consideration. 
Another panel, the Unity Team, is struggling to find state symbols acceptable to all.
In other news Thursday, France announced that new Defence Minister Herve Morin would visit Kosovo on Monday, in his first trip abroad. 
He will be meeting with KFOR Commander General Roland Kather about the transfer of the KFOR command to France in September. 
(RTK, Telegrafi, Kosovalive, AFP - 24/05/07)
